            'body_value' => '\'\'\'THIS PAGE CONTAINS INFORMATION ABOUT MY CURRENT RESIDENCE\'\'\'\r\n\r\nMy current residence is:\r\n* 800 North Magnolia\r\n* Lansing, MI 48912\r\n* Parcel Number: 33-01-01-11-353-061\r\n* Lansing City Assessor Online Page: https://is.bsasoftware.com/bsa.is/AssessingServices/ServiceAssessingDetails.aspx?dp=33-01-01-11-353-061&i=1&sna=Magnolia&snf=800&snt=801&appid=0&actSn=800&actSna=MAGNOLIA+AVE&actDir=N&unit=384\r\n\r\n!!NETWORK\r\n* See [[Home_Computers]] for much more detailed information on the network setup itself\r\n* Have run CAT-5 to all machines on first floor and basement\r\n\r\n!!ROOF\r\n* Done in 2010 by [[http://zischkebuilders.com/|Zischke Builders]]\r\n* local business\r\n* Katie is friends with Jesse Zischke\r\n* Added vents along underhang on side of house\r\n* Added vent along top of roof\r\n* Negated need for other side vents which were removed (I think, confirm by looking sometime)\r\n\r\n!!WINDOWS\r\n* Done in 2008 by Pinnacle Exteriors\r\n* Lifetime Warrenty on the windows and screens, including any type of damage, neighbors, pet, \'acts of god\', etc\r\n\r\n!!INSULATION\r\n* Apparently I have basically none inside the walls, and energy audit from 2009 showed\r\n* Attic insulated, but additional work done my myself and dad when moving in was incorrect, need to\r\n** Take down current insulation along roof slopes\r\n** Add styrofoam vents like what is currently along the edges all the way up to the top\r\n** Put current insulation back up\r\n** Finish insulation on side walls where we ran out\r\n\r\n!!SIDING\r\n* aluminum\r\n* still looks nice and should last nearly forever barring an insane hail storm\r\n* no intention of replacing while I am there\r\n\r\n!!STRUCTURAL\r\n* front porch slants downward because it\'s foundation is sinking slowly... conveniently provides nice drainage at current angle, have to do something about it someday if it gets worse\r\n* addon to kitchen with sub-basement also slopes slightly, noticeable in kitchen only because of clear dividing line between what was the addon and what wasn\'t, not really a serious structural issue\r\n* basement has seepage.  note this is different than it actually leaking or having foundation issues, foundation is firm, water leaks in slowly through the porous block foundation, gathers and drains in an amount that is never even measurable except where it pools on the way to drain, don\'t leave stuff on bare floor if it\'s water damagable\r\n \r\n\r\n',
