            'body_value' => '* stuff left for broad\r\n** sync script for our dev setup\r\n** confirm dev setup\r\n* consider moving /var/lib/nfs dirs\r\n** configure setting in /etc/default/nfs-common\r\n** configure setting in /etc/idmap.d\r\n* kernel opts worth setting for xen/standard\r\n** pci=nomsi (if pcix interrupts are causing issues [3.0.0-1 + intel GBeth/gbd driver)\r\n** pcie_aspm=off (advanced power management pcie features, similar scenario as above)\r\n** nmi_watchdog=0 (if watchdog hooks for CPUs are acting up at top of dmesg)\r\n** iommu=1 (xen hypervisor opt to enable iommu if motherboard supports it)\r\n* purge outdated databases on dev db server\r\n* further secure using ssl/tls where possible\r\n** svn.matrix.msu.edu\r\n** trac.matrix.msu.edu\r\n** dev2.matrix.msu.edu\r\n** ldap server?\r\n* kill application data folder for windows users\r\n* finish ruby server setup\r\n* debconf settings outdated entirely?\r\n* ln for /matrix on dfarm?\r\n* mail.matrix.msu.edu autodetect pointing to h-net stuff for matrix.msu.edu mail?\r\n* id/group resolution on macs\r\n* copy machine ldap\r\n** works using ldap1.matrix.msu.edu !!!!!!!!!!\r\n** won\'t work using ldap2.matrix.msu.edu (matrixdc03)\r\n** ldapro.system account had options changed\r\n*** don\'t require kerberos pre-auth (because the fucking logs were complaining)\r\n*** support des/128/256 enc types also currently set because it said trying type \'3\' which isn\'t supported\r\n*** see article http://pig.made-it.com/kerberos-etypes.html for more info on \'types\' which seems to indicate it\'s trying des\r\n* system times for sonic/tails (this is done, cept dom04 still starts with system time and not checking server on reboot)\r\n* For New Domain\r\n** remove DNS print.ad.matrix.msu.edu?\r\n* mdadm.conf should have e-mail address set so degraded array msgs get sent to useful people\r\n* when monthly updates update minor kernel version it fails to build <kernel-name>.fai initramfs\r\n* sysctl possible parameters\r\n** kernel.shmmni\r\n** kernel.shmall\r\n** kernel.shmmax\r\n** net.core.rmem_max\r\n** net.core.wmem_max\r\n** net.ipv4.tcp_rmem/wmem\r\n** swappiness\r\n* acpid - disable if no laptop/+keyboard special keys\r\n* when db is last accessed audit for our live and dev dbs\r\n* improve how php does it\'s logging\r\n** current work at peach:/etc/rsyslog.d/php.conf to redirect the right user log filter for php\r\n** gets other info as well\r\n* fix perms of /matrix/www after the permission change cock-up\r\n* E2 stuff that\'s left\r\n** binlongs no backup\r\n** useful URL info to documentation\r\n** Tor stats backlog processing\r\n** pw-protect stats.everything2?\r\n** duplicate mysql-zrm schedule created on webha, NO idea why??\r\n** kill of low/std ssh port on everything2 public iface\r\n** other stuff on zim, document the ext eth iface setup\r\n\r\n=== History\r\n* Bill Schoenl\'s computer, contact at 351-0456\r\n* Alex\r\n** Done by end of Apr\r\n** overlap w/ new student in Feb & March\r\n\r\n=== Done\r\n* lalorc site has db on wrong server for survey (no longer an issue cause they moved hosting)\r\n\r\n\r\n',
